# 100 Days of DSA with Java

This repository contains my journey of learning Data Structures and Algorithms (DSA) using Java over 100 days. Each day, I will solve problems, write code, and document my progress.

## Day 1: Java Basics
- Variables, Data Types, Input/Output
- Focus on understanding basic syntax and structure.
- Solve simple problems using loops and conditionals.

## Goals for Day 1
- Write Java code for basic input/output.
- Understand the concept of variables and data types.
- Learn how to write basic loops and conditions in Java.

## Progress
- [ ] Java Basics: Learned how to declare variables and use loops.
